<LP>
   SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Laserscope said it has received
expanded clearance from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration
to market a surgical laser system for all laparoscopic
general surgery.
   The FDA clearance permits use of the company's KTP/532
Surgical Laser Systems for a broad range of laparoscopic
procedures, including gall-bladder removal, appendectomies,
liver biopsies and hernias.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In 1988, Laserscope received FDA approval to market this
same laser system for endoscopic and open surgical
procedures.
